<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/fcd6a1f5821afb0a7f21ed8f654d5b5a.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 8 and c = 12. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.9</li><li>41.8</li><li>48.2</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{144}={64}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{144}-{64}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{80}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{80}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.9442719099992}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8.9}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{12}}\right)}}}\approx{41.810314895804}\approx{41.8}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{12}}\right)}}}\approx{48.189685104196}\approx{48.2}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

